verbose_text: While measuring urinary metabolites has an advantage over plasma samples as they are relatively unaffected by fluctuations due to different meal times (provided they are 12 or 24 h collections [XREF_BIBR], presently there does not appear to be an advantage for either AR or their metabolites, and the metabolites are yet to be assessed in larger populations (> 100 subjects) and at lower levels of AR intake (XREF_FIG).
